<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Yaglia Wins United Nations Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OCEANPORT, N.J. (AP) -- Yagli, the 1-10 favorite, cruised to a  
1 1/2-length victory Saturday in the $250,000 United Nations Handicap 
at Monmouth Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Yagli, trained by Bill Mott and ridden by Jerry Bailey, stayed  
unbeaten this year with his third straight victory, racing 1 3/8 miles 
over turf in 2:16, tying a track record. 
</P>
<P>
	Supreme Sound was second and Amerique was third in the field of  
six in the inaugural running of the UN at Monmouth Park, which took 
over the race when Atlantic City allowed it to lapse. 
</P>
<P>
	Yagli paid $2.20, $2.10 and $2.10. Supreme Sound was worth $2.80  
and $2.10 and Amerique returned $2.10 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	In the day's other feature, the $50,000 Tyro Stakes for  
2-year-olds, Outrigger rolled to a three-length score over House 
Burner, getting 5 1/2 furlongs over a fast main track in 1:03 4-5. 
</P>
<P>
	Bailey rode the winner, who paid $2.80, $2.20 and $2.10. House  
Burner returned $4 and $2.80 and Sky Legacy was worth $3.60 to 
show. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Outrigger's second win in two career starts.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
