<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Plane Crashes Involving Skydivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	A list of recent plane crashes involving skydivers:  
</P>
<P>
	-- In May 1997, a skydiving plane crashed in a field of sugar  
beets between Miami and the Everglades, killing a pilot and five 
skydivers. In that accident, one skydiver jumped out of the Cessna 
210-6 before the crash and safely floated to the ground. 
</P>
<P>
	-- In September 1997, five people were killed in Bremerton,  
Wash., when a one-engine Cessna 182 operated by a skydiving group 
plunged into a ravine. 
</P>
<P>
	-- In March 1998, a plane carrying members of a skydiving club  
crashed in Grain Valley, Mo., after reporting an electrical 
emergency shortly after takeoff. All six people on board the Cessna 
206 were killed. 
</P>
<P>
	-- In May, five skydivers and the pilot of their plane died when  
the aircraft crashed into a field in Celina, Ohio. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
