<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Killer, Victim's Kin in Same Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- The half-brother of slain Yosemite  
naturalist Joie Ruth Armstrong is being held at the same jail where 
his sister's confessed killer is in custody. 
</P>
<P>
	Brady Schwartz, 18, is accused of stealing more than $18,000  
from his family to pay off a drug debt. 
</P>
<P>
	Schwartz's bond was raised Friday from $2,000 to $25,000, and he  
was ordered held at the Fresno County Jail, where Cary Stayner 
awaits an Aug. 6 arraignment in U.S. District Court on a murder 
charge in the July 21 death of Armstrong. 
</P>
<P>
	Armstrong, who led outdoor education programs for the Yosemite  
Institute, was beheaded July 21. The 26-year-old's body was found 
the next day near her home inside the park. 
</P>
<P>
	Stayner has reportedly confessed to Armstrong's murder and the  
slayings earlier this year of Carole Sund, her daughter Juli, and 
family friend Silvina Pelosso. They were last seen alive Feb. 15 at 
the Cedar Lodge where Stayner was living and working as a handyman. 
</P>
<P>
	No charges have been filed in the Sund-Pelosso murders. FBI  
agents and prosecutors are scheduled to meet Monday in Fresno to 
discuss which county will eventually prosecute the case. 
</P>
<P>
	Schwartz, who shares the same mother as Armstrong but lives with  
his father, was arrested July 18 after his father, a broker, 
discovered $3,300 in cash and $15,000 in cashier's checks missing 
from their home. 
</P>
<P>
	Schwartz, who at first denied stealing the money, told the judge  
Friday that he decided to tell the truth in the wake of his 
sister's death, saying his conscience got the best of him. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
