<HEADLINE> Sears To Cut 680 Jobs by October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOFFMAN ESTATES, Ill. (AP) -- Sears, Roebuck and Co. will trim  
about 680 jobs from its corporate headquarters by the end of 
October, the company says. 
</P>
<P>
	The cuts will affect 10 percent of the company's headquarters  
staff in addition to hundreds of independent contractors who will 
be let go by Aug. 31. 
</P>
<P>
	``By year-end, we will have a leaner organization,'' said Sears  
spokesman Ron Culp. 
</P>
<P>
	Sears has been under increasing market pressure from  
lower-priced competitors, such as Wal-Mart Stores Inc. and Target. 
</P>
<P>
	The company's same-store sales have increased only 1 percent to  
2 percent during each of the past several months and second-quarter 
profits fell 1.5 percent to $331 million, Sears reported last week. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
