<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Atlas 3, El Salvador 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Jorge Santillana scored twice in the first 19  
minutes to lead Atlas of Guadalajara to a 3-2 victory over El 
Salvador's national team Saturday night in the Coliseum Cup soccer 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Atlas, runnerup in Mexico's First Division this season, claimed  
third place by winning the first game of Saturday night's 
doubleheader at the Memorial Coliseum. 
</P>
<P>
	Guatemala was playing Atletico Morelia of Mexico in the final.  
</P>
<P>
	Santillana scored his first goal in the 12th minute when he beat  
goalkeeper Sergio Munoz on a breakaway. 
</P>
<P>
	Seven minutes later, Santillana redirected Juan Pablo Garcia's  
cross from the right wing with his left foot to give Atlas a 2-0 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Juan Urteaga added what proved to be the winning goal when he  
deflected another cross from Garcia in the 23rd minute. 
</P>
<P>
	El Salvador's Ernesto Gochez and Alexander Amaya del Cid scored  
in the 44th and 50th minutes, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
	Atlas played with 10 men during second-half stoppage time after  
midfielder Jorge Almiron received a red card in the 90th minute. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
