<HEADLINE> Loaded Gun Wins Philly Breeders Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BENSALEM, Pa. (AP) -- Jose Flores steered Loaded Gun outside of  
the leaders while turning into the homestretch and then kept his 
mount under strong pressure for a 1 1/4-length victory in the $200,000 
Philadelphia Park Breeders' Cup Handicap on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Four-year-old Loaded Gun was in second place after a  
quarter-mile behind Power by Far, the eventual third-place 
finisher, when he pushed for the lead with a quarter-mile 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
	Flores credited owner-trainer Janice Gerace with instructions  
that gave Loaded Gun the win. 
</P>
<P>
	``Miss Janice told me to go to the outside and then work it out  
from there. He just dragged me to the front.'' Flores said. 
</P>
<P>
	Loaded Gun's strong finish helped fight off the 7-to-10 favorite  
Artax, which overcame a walking start from the gate to finish 
second. 
</P>
<P>
	Loaded Gun cover six furlongs in 1:08 4-5 to earn $60,000 for  
Ms. Gerace. His lifetime earnings stand at $275,180. 
</P>
<P>
	Loaded Gun returned $22.60, $5.80 and $4. Artax paid $3 and  
$2.40, and Power by Far was worth $5.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Loaded Gun will return to Monmouth Park, N.J., to await a sprint  
stake there, Ms. Gerace said. 
  	   	
</P>
