<HEADLINE> CBS Assistant Charged in Mishap  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CROMWELL, Conn. (AP) -- An assistant to CBS golf commentator Gary  
McCord ran over the foot of a volunteer with a golf cart at the 
Greater Hartford Open. 
</P>
<P>
	Steven Lewison, 46, is charged with second-degree reckless  
endangerment. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewison and McCord were driving to a broadcast tower Thursday  
when they came across the volunteer marshal, who was roping off an 
area on the third hole. She told the pair the route they had chosen 
was off-limits, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Lewison refused to listen to her,'' Cromwell Police Capt.  
Thomas Roohr said. ``He continued on and in the process of doing so 
ran over her foot.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The marshal, whose name was not released, was treated at the  
tournament's medical service station. The extent of her injuries 
was unclear. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewison, from Wisconsin, is free on $500 bond and is due back in  
court Aug. 10. 
</P>
<P>
	``We at CBS, and certainly Gary McCord, would feel very sorry if  
someone got hurt over a misunderstanding,'' said LeslieAnne Wade, a 
spokeswoman for CBS Sports. 
</P>
