<HEADLINE> Tigers, Marlins Swap Prospects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- The Florida Marlins and Detroit Tigers  
exchanged minor league pitching prospects Saturday night, with 
Florida sending right-hander Brandon Villafuerte to Detroit for 
right-hander Mike Drumright. 
</P>
<P>
	Drumright, 25, was the Tigers' first-round selection and the  
11th overall pick in the June 1995 draft, but has struggled with 
his control in the minors. 
</P>
<P>
	A former Wichita State teammate of Marlins reliever Braden  
Looper, the 6-foot-4 Drumright was 6-10 with a 5.97 ERA and 59 
walks in 120 2-3 innings at Triple-A Toledo. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's like a lot of pitchers scuffling in Triple-A, he needs to  
work on his command,'' Marlins general manager Dave Dombrowski 
said. ``He has a big, strong pitcher's body who has thrown strikes 
in the past and has an above-average fastball.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Villafuerte, 25, was 6-8 with a 3.50 ERA at Double-A Portland.  
He was originally acquired by Florida in the March 1998 deal that 
sent left-hander Al Leiter to the New York Mets. 
</P>
<P>
	Drumright, who was on the Tigers' 40-man roster, was assigned to  
Triple-A Calgary. The Marlins also designated right-hander Archie 
Corbin for assignment and replaced him on the active roster with 
right-hander Rafael Medina from Triple-A Calgary. 
</P>
