<HEADLINE> Eastwood Part Owner of Pebble Beach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PEBBLE BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Clint Eastwood, along with a few  
other prominent investors, is now the proud owner of one of the 
world's most famous golf courses. 
</P>
<P>
	On Friday, an $820 million deal to buy Pebble Beach Co. from the  
Lone Express Co., a subsidiary of Japanese golf resort operator 
Taiheiyo Club Inc., was finalized. 
</P>
<P>
	Besides Eastwood, the new ownership group includes pro golfer  
Arnold Palmer and former baseball commissioner Peter Ueberroth. 
</P>
<P>
	Plans are under way to develop a new course and build 300 homes  
on Pebble Beach. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
