<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mariners Activate Tom Davey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- The Seattle Mariners on Saturday added 6-foot-7  
right-hander Tom Davey to their 25-man roster and optioned 
right-hander Ken Cloude to Triple-A Tacoma for the second time this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Davey, 25, was acquired along with left-hander Steve Sinclair in  
a trade with Toronto on Wednesday for first baseman David Segui. 
</P>
<P>
	Davey reported to the Mariners on Saturday. He immediately was  
added to the team's bullpen. 
</P>
<P>
	Davey split this season between the Blue Jays and Triple-A  
Syracuse, going 1-1 with one save and a 4.70 ERA with Toronto 
before he was sent down June 28. He was 1-2 with a 3.48 ERA at 
Syracuse. 
</P>
<P>
	Cloude, 24, has been a major disappointment for the Mariners  
this season. He began the season at Tacoma. In 26 games, including 
four starts, in Seattle, he had a 3-4 record and a 7.84 ERA in 59 
2-3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Cloude was an eight-game winner in 30 starts for the Mariners  
last season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
