<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Astros Place Eusebio on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- The Houston Astros placed catcher Tony Eusebio  
on the 15-day disabled list Saturday with a strained left 
hamstring. 
</P>
<P>
	Eusebio was hurt in the Astros' 4-2 loss at Colorado on  
Thursday. He was hitting .259 with two home runs and 15 RBIs. The 
move is retroactive to Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Astros purchased the contract of catcher Randy Knorr from  
Triple-A New Orleans, bringing him up for the second time in July. 
Knorr played in five games when Eusebio was sidelined after 
suffering a bruised left eye at Cincinnati on July 5. 
</P>
<P>
	Knorr made three starts, going 1-for-13. He was batting .337  
with 13 doubles, eight homers and 31 RBIs for New Orleans. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
