<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rapids 2, Burn 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Wolde Harris' early goal proved to be the  
game-winner as the Colorado Rapids extended their lead in the 
Western Conference with a 2-0 victory Saturday over the Dallas 
Burn. 
</P>
<P>
	Harris scored in the eighth minute, fighting through the Dallas  
defense at the top of the box and sending a shot past Burn (10-11) 
goalkeeper Matt Jordan into the left post. Harris leads the Rapids 
with eight goals this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Colorado (14-5) won its seventh game in 10 games on the road  
this year. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rapids were able to win without six of their usual starters.  
Three players -- Paul Bravo, Marcelo Balboa and Matt Mckeon -- are 
playing on the U.S. national team at the FIFA Confederations Cup in 
Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	Three other starters missed the match with injuries.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
