<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19990731.0088 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 20:00:09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Padres activate Chris Gomez </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Shortstop Chris Gomez, who missed 52 games  
after undergoing double knee surgery, was activated Saturday night 
by the San Diego Padres and started against the Houston Astros. 
</P>
<P>
	Gomez took the roster spot vacated when the Padres traded  
utilityman Jim Leyritz to the New York Yankees for a minor league 
pitcher earlier Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Gomez was recalled from a 10-game rehabilitation assignment to  
Class AAA Las Vegas, where he hit .333 with four RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	Gomez, bothered by knee pain most of the season, underwent  
arthroscopic surgery on June 4 to repair a small cartilage tear in 
his left knee and had rough cartilage smoothed in both joints. 
</P>
<P>
	Gomez was hitting .222 with no homers and three RBIs before  
going on the DL on June 4. 
</P>
<P>
	Rookie Damian Jackson, who had made several starts at shortstop  
before Gomez went on the DL, started all but one game while Gomez 
was out. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
