<HEADLINE> Bolero Master Wins at Yonkers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	YONKERS, N.Y. (AP) -- Bolero Master, with Hall of Fame driver  
John Campbell, overtook favored Island Fantasy in the final eighth 
of a mile to win the $303,995 Art Rooney Memorial Pace at Yonkers 
Raceway on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Bolero Master went a mile in 1:53 4-5 in winning for the second  
time in six starts this year. The victory was worth $151,997, 
almost twice his previous earnings of $86,175. 
</P>
<P>
	Bolero Master, who left from the rail in the eight-horse field,  
was second after a quarter-mile and was third when the field 
crossed the finish line the first time. 
</P>
<P>
	Still third after three-quarters of a mile, Bolero Master caught  
Island Fantasy at the top of the stretch and held on by a 
quarter-length. Justanotherpoorboy was third. 
</P>
<P>
	Bolero Master returned $19.80, $6.70 and $3.60.  
</P>
<P>
	``Leaving from the rail was the key,'' Campbell said. ``This was  
a huge win for Bolero Master. As for myself, I've been very 
fortunate at Yonkers. This is another big stakes win for me on this 
very comfortable track.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The race is named for the late owner of the Pittsburgh Steelers.  
  	   	
</P>
