<HEADLINE> 'Radar' Back On His Feet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Dropping of the radar screen cost Gary Burgoff,  
best known for his portrayal of ``Radar'' in ``M A S H,'' a good 
deal of cash over the years. 
</P>
<P>
	Burghoff told the Aug. 9 edition of People that his decision to  
turn down acting roles after his seven year stint on the popular 
series reduced his income sharply, and he was forced to file for 
bankruptcy in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was down to my last $500,'' the 56-year-old said. ``The  
money ran out.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But the actor is in financial shape these days. He sells his  
canvas drawings of wildlife for $25,000 each; he is acting on stage 
again, and is soon to appear in the 120-city tour of Neil Simon's 
``The Last of the Red Hot Lovers''; and is the new host of the 
public television series, ``Pets: Part of the Family.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
