<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wizards 3, Clash 2, SO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Backup goalie David Winner stopped four  
of five San Jose shots in a shootout Saturday as the Kansas City 
Wizards beat the Clash 3-2. 
</P>
<P>
	Vincente Figueroa and Chris Brown scored for the Wizards (6-14)  
in the shootout. 
</P>
<P>
	Mauricio Wright scored for San Jose (11-9) off a corner kick  
from Scott Bower with five minutes left in regulation to force the 
shootout. 
</P>
<P>
	Preki Radosavlijevic had both goals in regulation for Kansas  
City. 
</P>
<P>
	Mauricio Solis scored the first goal of the game to give the  
Clash an early lead. 
</P>
<P>
	San Jose still leads the MSL in shootout victories with a 9-2  
record. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
