<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Twenty Hurt in Car-Bus Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DOWNERS GROVE, Ill. (AP) -- Twenty factory workers were injured,  
some seriously, when a car driven by an alleged drunken driver 
slammed into the back of a bus that was carrying them to work, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	Several passengers were ejected from the small bus about 10 p.m.  
Friday after the collision caused it to hit a power pole on 
Interstate 355 and tip over, police Master Sgt. Luis Tigera said. 
</P>
<P>
	The bus was headed from an employment agency's pickup point in  
suburban Cicero to TDI Batteries Inc. in Downers Grove. The 
passengers were on their way to work the overnight shift at the 
factory, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	At least 18 people were hospitalized, including three who were  
in intensive care, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver of the BMW that collided with the bus was also  
injured. She was charged with driving under the influence after 
flunking a sobriety test, state police said. Her identity was not 
released. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
