<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jags Sign Linebacker Lonnie Marts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- The Jacksonville Jaguars signed  
free-agent linebacker Lonnie Marts on Saturday to take the place of 
the injured Bryce Paup. 
</P>
<P>
	Marts, a nine-year veteran, started 15 games with the Tennessee  
Oilers last season. He has also started for the Kansas City Chiefs 
and Tampa Bay Buccaneers. 
</P>
<P>
	Marts signed a one-year deal worth $600,000 plus incentives.  
</P>
<P>
	``He's a quality linebacker, he has started, he has experience  
and he wants to be here,'' said Jaguars coach Tom Coughlin. ``It's 
a good note for our team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Tennessee released Marts to make room for rookie Jevon Kearse  
and quarterback Neil O'Donnell. 
</P>
<P>
	Paup, who is recovering from a torn pectoral muscle, is expected  
to miss at least the first preseason game, probably more. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
