<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Recent Atlanta Shootings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Recent shootings in the Atlanta area involving multiple victims:  
</P>
<P>
	--May 20: Six students at Heritage High School in suburban  
Rockdale County are wounded by a 15-year-old sophomore who fired 14 
shots from a .22-caliber rifle and .357-caliber Magnum revolver he 
had concealed in the pants leg of his jeans and a book bag. 
</P>
<P>
	--July 12: Six members of a southwest Atlanta family -- two  
sisters and four children of one of the women -- are fatally shot by 
the live-in boyfriend of the children's mother. The gunman then 
kills himself, leaving one 11-year-old survivor. 
</P>
<P>
	--July 23: Two Cobb County SWAT team members are mortally wounded  
when they storm the home of a man in suburban Austell after he shot 
and wounded another police officer who responded to a complaint of 
a neighborhood disturbance. The gunman is shot while trying to get 
out a bathroom window the following morning. 
</P>
<P>
	--July 29: Nine people in two offices buildings in Atlanta's  
Buckhead section are shot to death and 13 are wounded by a day 
stock trader, who officials say may have been upset over financial 
losses. Police in Henry County find three dead relatives of the 
suspect in Stockbridge, 16 miles southeast of Atlanta. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
