<HEADLINE> Mets Get Dunston for Paquette </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- The New York Mets picked up veteran infielder  
Shawon Dunston from the St. Louis Cardinals just before the trading 
deadline Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Dunston, who broke out of an 0-for-24 slump with two hits  
Saturday, is batting .307 with five homers and 25 RBIs in 150 
at-bats. He cost the Mets minor league infielder Craig Paquette, 
30, who was assigned to Triple-A Memphis. 
</P>
<P>
	Paquette is currently with the U.S. Pan American team. He hit a  
two-run home run Thursday in an upset of Cuba in Winnipeg. 
</P>
<P>
	Dunston has been a shortstop most of his career, but has also  
played some outfield the last few years. 
  	   	
