<HEADLINE> Rapper ODB Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Russell Jones, also known as rapper ODB, was  
arrested early Saturday in Queens, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police stopped Jones, 30, on Linden Boulevard at about 2:45 a.m.  
after he allegedly ran a red light in his 1994 Mercedes 
convertible. Officers arrested Jones when they learned he was 
driving with a suspended license. 
