<HEADLINE> Worker Kills Boss, Self in N.C. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- A maintenance worker shot and killed  
himself after fatally shooting his supervisor at a local trucking 
terminal. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said George Edward Moore, 58, entered the terminal Friday  
afternoon, warned other employees to get out of the way, and then 
shot Scott Simpson, 47, with a handgun. 
</P>
<P>
	``This was not a random shooting,'' said police spokesman Keith  
Bridges. ``He intended to kill him. There was obviously something 
between the two.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Derrick Hooker, who works on the loading docks at Watkins Motor  
Lines, said he spoke with Moore just hours before the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
	``He told me the supervisor was messing with him,'' Hooker said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
