<HEADLINE> Marine Aircraft Crashes, 2 Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAMP PENDLETON, Calif. (AP) -- A military helicopter hovering  
about five feet above the ground flipped over and crashed Friday at 
Camp Pendleton, injuring two Marines. 
</P>
<P>
	One pilot was hospitalized with minor injuries, said Maj.  
Stephen Kay, a Marine Corps spokesman. A second pilot suffered very 
light injuries, he added. 
</P>
<P>
	The accident with the Cobra light-attack helicopter occurred at  
12:09 p.m. during a routine training exercise at the Marine base 
north of San Diego, Kay said. 
</P>
<P>
	The names of the pilots were not immediately released, and the  
cause of the accident was under investigation. 
  	   	
</P>
