<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 22:40:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Guatemala 4, Morelia 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Guatemala overcame two ejections to defeat  
Mexico's Atletico Morelia 4-2 on penalty kicks to win the Coliseum 
Cup soccer tournament Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Both teams played to a 1-1 draw after regulation in the second  
game of a doubleheader at the Memorial Coliseum. 
</P>
<P>
	Another Mexican club, Atlas of Guadalajara, took third place  
with a 3-2 victory against El Salvador in the first game. 
</P>
<P>
	Guatemala played with nine players in stoppage time.  
</P>
<P>
	Jorge Perez received his second yellow card in the 42nd minute,  
and Nelson Caceres got a red card in the 90th minute. Referee Tim 
Weyland issued nine yellow cards and two red cards. 
</P>
<P>
	Goalkeeper Julio Engleton made two saves during the penalty-kick  
sequence. 
</P>
<P>
	Alex Fernandez's soft shot hit Engleton's feet as the goalkeeper  
dived to his right. Then Engleton dived to his left to stop Jose 
Luis Malibran's weak shot to the right post. 
</P>
<P>
	Guatemala's Everaldo Valencia, who had suffered from back spasms  
during Friday's practice, converted his kick to secure the victory. 
</P>
<P>
	Morelia took a 1-0 lead when Fernandez scored in the 73rd  
minute. Carlos Morales' low cross from the left wing sailed threw 
the legs of a Morelia forward to Fernandez, who converted from 15 
yards. 
</P>
<P>
	One minute later, Nolly Sanchez tied the score with a 16-yard  
shot inside the left post. Sanchez entered the game in the 70th 
minute. 
</P>
<P>
	In the third-place game, Jorge Santillana scored twice in the  
first 19 minutes to lead Atlas. Teammate Juan Urteaga added what 
proved to be the winning goal in the 23rd minute. 
</P>
<P>
	El Salvador's Ernesto Gochez and Alexander Amaya del Cid scored  
in the 44th and 50th minutes, respectively. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
