<DOCNO> APW19990731.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 19:10:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> King Agree to Contract With Bucs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Quarterback Shaun King, a second-round draft  
pick of the Tampa Bay Buccaneers, agreed to terms of a four-year 
contract worth more than $2 million on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The former Tulane star was the 50th player selected after  
leading the Green Wave to their first unbeaten season since 1931. 
He will compete with Eric Zeier for the No. 2 job behind Trent 
Dilfer. 
</P>
<P>
	The agreement leaves first-round pick Anthony McFarland, a  
defensive tackle from LSU, as the only Bucs rookie who hasn't come 
to terms. Players report to training camp Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	King, who grew up in St. Petersburg, started 39 of 41 games he  
played at Tulane and set Green Wave career records for total 
offense (9,468 yards), passing yards (8,419), touchdown passes 
(70), completions (646) and pass attempts (1,163). 
</P>
<P>
	He threw at least one TD pass in the final 19 games of his  
college career. Last season, he set a NCAA record with a passing 
efficiency rating of 183.3 while completing 68 percent of his 
attempts for 3,232 yards and 36 TDs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
